@page "/enigma-game-mechanics"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma System Mechanics | Rooms, Puzzles, Rewards, and Sectors"
         Description="Learn the core mechanics behind room progression, puzzle states, sector ownership, field-tool usage, and research-linked progression."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma mechanics, anomaly sectors, Maze Nuggets, puzzle systems, research council" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <div>
                <span class="profile-kicker">System Mechanics</span>
                <h1>Enigma Operational Mechanics</h1>
            </div>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/home">Back</a>
        </div>
        <p>Enigma combines direct movement, room-based puzzle states, persistent sector ownership, and research systems that carry progression between expeditions.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Room Structure</h2>
        <h3>Start, Reward, and Finish Rooms</h3>
        <p>Every sector includes a start room, finish room, and intermediate rooms. Layout and door connectivity are generated from the seed.</p>
        <h3>In-Room Interaction</h3>
        <p>Most interactions happen directly on the stage. Console overlays appear only when precision puzzle input is needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Puzzle Systems</h2>
        <h3>Stage Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Spatial mechanics like pressure plates, route checks, and activation zones are solved directly inside the room.</p>
        <h3>Overlay Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Logic, memory, and timing variants open in the room console and return results to the shared room state.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Sector Lifecycle</h2>
        <h3>Discovery and Ownership</h3>
        <p>Sector discovery is tied to real completion. Ownership can transfer later through exchange actions without rewriting the original discovery history.</p>
        <h3>Listing, Analysis, and Locks</h3>
        <p>Owned sectors can be listed on the exchange or assigned to analysis for daily MN. Sectors under analysis are lock-protected and cannot be sold or recycled until lock conditions expire.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Progression and Power</h2>
        <h3>MN and Field-Tool Flow</h3>
        <p>Run outcomes, daily systems, and research interactions update your MN balance and field-tool availability.</p>
        <h3>Governance Weighting</h3>
        <p>Council power is based on MN spent and a capped multiplier model that factors analyzed sectors and participation history.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Continue Orientation</h2>
        <div class="seo-link-grid">
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/about">
                <strong>Program Brief</strong>
                <span>How Enigma Corporation and A.R.D connect explorers, sectors, and governance.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/how-enigma-works">
                <strong>Operations Guide</strong>
                <span>Step-by-step expedition flow and how outcomes feed A.R.D systems.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/enigma-multiplayer">
                <strong>Co-op Operations</strong>
                <span>Shared command sessions, live invites, synchronized movement, and co-op completion.</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
